These pistols have a lot of interesting history, and this one is in great shape! THIS IS NOT AN NFA ITEM. In order to import these pistols into the United States, they had to meet certain size/weight requirements so a nonfunctional suppressor was "permanently" pinned and welded onto the barrel. I've since removed it, which makes the pistol much more usable(the suppressor blocks the sight picture and makes it uncomfortably front heavy), however you can still easily thread it back on/off if you'd like. These are rarely in stock with KA and highly sought after for M-16 clone projects.from KA webpage:The KAC M5 RAS (Rail Adapter System) was developed for use on the US military's M16A4, and with hundreds of thousands of rails issued to date, it is one of the most battle proven designs available for the AR-15 platform. This non-free float handguard is a simple-to-install, drop-in upgrade that features genuine Mil-Spec M1913 Picatinny Rails along its entire length. What sets the M5 RAS apart from other 2-piece quad rails on the market is that it securely locks to the rifle's barrel nut via a clamp and screw arrangement, making it a very solid foundation upon which to mount tactical accessories. Includes three KAC 11 Rib Rail Panels. These KAC M5 RAS Seconds are functionally identical to our "Firsts," but may have slight blemishes. These blemishes can come in the form of scratches, dings, slightly darker or lighter anodizing, or crooked or backward lasering.
